The '''Battle Group of [[Yun-Q'aah]]''', was one of the five primary Battle Groups used by the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] during the [[Battle of Ebaq]].

==History==
Under the command of [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Droog'an]], the Yun-Q'aah Battle Group worked with the [[Battle Group of Yun-Txiin|Battle Group]] of [[Yun-Txiin]] to initially engage the squadron under the command of [[General/Legends|General]] [[Keyan Farlander/Legends|Keyan Farlander]]. Their working together to attack the enemy was in homage of the [[Lover Gods]] they were named in honor of. When the [[Smugglers' Alliance]] fleet arrived, the Battle Group of Yun-Q'aah engaged them. When [[Warmaster]] [[Tsavong Lah]] ordered the fleets to withdraw, the Battle Group of Yun-Q'aah received enough of a warning about the minefield the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] had established to ward off critical damage.

